    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle M_{i}h_{i}\eq=
uiv 1{\pmod {m_{i}}}\,.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/ed2433873b4e6d1c11fc1d5a42d3e0f1720a2e0f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:23.011ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle M_=
{i}h_{i}\equiv 1{\pmod {m_{i}}}\,.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>With these numbers <i>h</i><sub><i>i</i></sub>, any integer <i>x</i> can=
 be reconstructed from its remainders <i>x</i><sub><i>i</i></sub> by the eq=
uation
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e x\equiv (x_{1}M_{1}h_{1}+x_{2}M_{2}h_{2}+\cdots +x_{N}M_{N}h_{N}){\pmod {=
M}}\,.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
