</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/3d0bf20425d35b1e9a42b85e40630f5c1263661f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -5.671ex; width:19.863ex; height:12.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {=
\begin{aligned}&amp;\gcd(3,4)&amp;\leftarrow \\=3D{}&amp;\gcd(3,1)&amp;\rig=
htarrow \\=3D{}&amp;\gcd(2,1)&amp;\rightarrow \\=3D{}&amp;\gcd(1,1).\end{al=
igned}}}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>The Euclidean algorithm has almost the same relationship to another bina=
ry tree on the rational numbers called the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Calkin%E2%80%93Wilf_tree" title=3D"Calkin=E2=80=93Wilf tree">Calki=
n=E2=80=93Wilf tree</a>. The difference is that the path is reversed: inste=
ad of producing a path from the root of the tree to a target, it produces a=
 path from the target to the root.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Continued_fractions">Contin=
ued fractions</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=
=3DEuclidean_algorithm&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D21" title=3D"Edit se=
ction: Continued fractions"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The Euclidean algorithm has a close relationship with <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continued_fraction" title=3D"Continued fraction">con=
tinued fractions</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Vinogradov_1954_80-0" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_algorithm#cite_n=
ote-Vinogradov_1954-80"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>79<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The sequence of equations can be writt=
en in the form
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\begin{aligned}{\frac {a}{b}}&amp;=3Dq_{0}+{\frac {r_{0}}{b}}\\{\frac {b=
}{r_{0}}}&amp;=3Dq_{1}+{\frac {r_{1}}{r_{0}}}\\{\frac {r_{0}}{r_{1}}}&amp;=
=3Dq_{2}+{\frac {r_{2}}{r_{1}}}\\&amp;\,\,\,\vdots \\{\frac {r_{k-2}}{r_{k-=
1}}}&amp;=3Dq_{k}+{\frac {r_{k}}{r_{k-1}}}\\&amp;\,\,\,\vdots \\{\frac {r_{=
N-2}}{r_{N-1}}}&amp;=3Dq_{N}\,.\end{aligned}}}">
