is likewise "noisy".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-103" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_algorithm#cite_note-103"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>102<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up>
</p><p>To reduce this noise, a second average <i>=CF=84</i>(<i>a</i>) is ta=
ken over all numbers coprime with <i>a</i>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
